article.headline: Siena 93, Manhattan 69
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. -- Kenny Hasbrouck scored 23 points to help Siena rout Manhattan 93-69 on senior night Thursday. Clarence Jackson added 21 points and Edwin Ubiles had 20 for Siena (20-6, 14-1 MAAC), which beat Manhattan for the seventh time in eight meetings. Darryl Crawford scored 22 points for the Jaspers (14-11, 8-7 MAAC). Chris Smith added 17. The Saints were 6-24 in 2004-05, the year before Hasbrouck arrived. Hasbrouck, head coach Fran McCaffery's first recruit, led the Saints to a win over Vanderbilt in last year's NCAA tournament. Siena jumped out to a 21-6 lead and took a 47-31 edge into the halftime break en route to its highest scoring game of the year.
